OL,3,C1 in 5 drinkers in Wales putting their
OL,4,Chealth at 'serious risk', charity warns
OL,6,FCompared to drinkers across the UK,
OL,7,Foverall drinkers in Wales are less
OL,8,Flikely to drink both zero-alcohol and
OL,9,Flow-alcohol products.
OL,11,FBut they are popular among younger
OL,12,Fdrinkers (18`34-year-olds), with 43%
OL,13,Fcurrently drinking zero- or low-
OL,14,Falcohol drinks compared to 35% of
OL,15,Fthose aged 55 or above.
OL,17,FKaren Tyrell, CEO of Drinkaware, said
OL,18,Fthe increase in moderation is
OL,19,F"encouraging".
